Download
  http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/sed/sed-4.0.7.tar.gz
to /tmp/ .

Validate:
  /tmp[0]$md5sum sed-4.0.7.tar.gz
  005738e7f97bd77d95b6907156c8202a  sed-4.0.7.tar.gz

Extract archive:
  /tmp[0]$gzip --decompress sed-4.0.7.tar.gz
  /tmp[0]$tar --extract --file sed-4.0.7.tar

Build with MSYS:
  wboutin@OWNER /c/tmp/sed-4.0.7
  $ ./configure && make

Copy binary to path:
  mm39272@MM39272PC /c/tmp/sed-4.0.7/sed
  $ cp --force --parents --preserve --recursive sed.exe /c/usr/bin/

* Install wx

...
The following options must be set to 1 in wx/setup.h (or using configure):
    wxUSE_DOC_VIEW_ARCHITECTURE
    wxUSE_MDI_ARCHITECTURE
    wxUSE_PRINTING_ARCHITECTURE
    wxUSE_STD_STRING

The following options must be set to 0 (all these are on by default):
    wxUSE_APPLE_IEEE
    wxUSE_LIBJPEG
    wxUSE_LIBTIFF
    wxUSE_GIF
    wxUSE_THREADS


* Platform-specific instructions

No special instructions are needed for GNU/Linux: on that platform,
everything will just work.

* Platform: msw

On the msw platform, it is necessary to install a compiler, a shell,
and certain general-purpose utilities that GNU/Linux systems provide
by default.

* Install MinGW

If an earlier release of MinGW already exists then this discussion
is useful prior to installing the newer release:
  http://gcc.gnu.org/ml/gcc-patches/2004-06/msg00703.html

Download
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/binutils-2.15.91-20040904-1.tar.gz
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/gcc-core-3.4.2-20040916-1.tar.gz
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/gcc-g++-3.4.2-20040916-1.tar.gz
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/gdb-5.2.1-1.exe
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/mingw-runtime-3.7.tar.gz
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/mingw-utils-0.3.tar.gz
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/mingw32-make-3.80.0-3.tar.gz
  http://umn.dl.sourceforge.net/sourceforge/mingw/w32api-3.2.tar.gz
to /tmp/ .

